</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">Keep printheads in shape by not shutting down the engine, but keep the engine in Keep-healthy mode. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">Printheads are kept in shape during the keep-healthy mode of the engine(low power mode). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When this process is not working well (eg : shut down of engine or MRE) the ink on the nozzleplate dries out. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This will lead to multiple side-shooters or even blocked nozzles.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In most cases these nozzles will recover when the printhead is used again.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> However in case of long shut-down period these blockades can be permanent. In those cases 
<xref keyref="PQ_06" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-DE30DA84-5466-45C9-93CF-F2EFE11A1875.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Graininess in the whole image?>Graininess in the whole image</xref> might appear. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-945E6C60-1212-47DF-9487-92374227D4B4.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
